node.text: JC and Henok make time to catch up on their friendship that formed during the first Rate Beer fest and how Omnipollo's intriguing intersection of beer, pop culture and artistic exploration resonates so much with JC. Fast forward today and hear about how @omnipollo beer is available all over the world while at the same time setting down deeper roots in Sweden. We hit refresh on Covered In Puppies, our collaboration DIPA and its drinking beautifully. We miss you Henok & Karl!

node.text:
You're likely asking yourself, "It's now late August, where the heck is Headroom?!"

Originally brewed in 2015 for the Hop Jam music and beer festival, Headroom and its sibling Max Headroom represent the pinnacle of our hop-forward brewing program. Laden with ridiculous amounts of Galaxy hops, these beers are released just once annually, resulting in our most anticipated weekend of the year.

Galaxy holds a very special place in Trillium's history. When it's really singing, there's nothing quite like its explosive notes of overripe pineapple, creamy orange sorbet, and juicy peach. Many might not remember, but in the very early days of Trillium, we held off brewing an IPA until we could secure enough Galaxy for even a few 10bbl batches of our first and flagship IPA, Congress Street.

The world has seen many supply chain interruptions across almost all industries in the past 17 months. Beer is not exempt from these disturbances, particularly when it comes to raw ingredients. Our 2021 Galaxy contract has been severely delayed due to shortages in refrigerated shipping containers and overall global logistics log jams.

Congress Street, Vicinity, Headroom, and other Galaxy-centric hoppy beers will return if/when we can secure our 2021 harvest contracts, assuming that they pass through our selection process and meet the standards we've historically set for these beers.

Citra, Mosaic, El Dorado, Nelson, Motueka, Strata (etc) have all had their best crop years to date in our opinion, so if there's a silver lining to the situation, it's that the other beers in our portfolio have seen some of their most impressive releases to-date. But you don't need to tell us that there's nothing quite like peak Galaxy. 

So what does that mean for the near term? Well, we pride ourselves on the ability to pivot and face challenges head-on. If we can't brew Headroom, we're going to welcome a new addition to the family. More details coming very soon!

📸  @michaelcwoodjr

node.text:
Riesling absolutely shimmers on the palate, bringing excitement and velocity to the drinking experience. While we've utilized Germany's most planted white grape variety in a "Dialed" beer before, we've never applied it to the cornerstone Double IPA of the series, Dialed-In.

Pairing Citra and Mosaic with Riesling juice conjures notes of ripe apricot, fuzzy donut peach, and juicy nectarine. It's a stunning combination and we can't wait for you to try it!

Cans are now available to order online for Pickup and UPS Direct home delivery to MA, DC, KY, NE, NH, PA, and VT. $22.20/4-pack, limit one case per person.

In August of 2020, we released our take on Black is Beautiful Imperial Stout with our friends at White Lion Brewing as part of an international movement to directly address police brutality and the legal injustices that American people of color face every day.

This project saw participation from over 1,200 breweries in 22 countries, raising much-needed awareness for inequity and funds for organizations that are putting in the work towards equality and inclusion.

The founder of Black is Beautiful is Marcus Baskerville, Owner and Head Brewer at Weathered Souls Brewing. We got to know Marcus through this project and quickly became fond of his lineup of beers, in particular the impressive array of Imperial and Barrel-Aged Stouts that the brewery releases on a regular basis. 

When the opportunity arose to collaborate on a beer together, we noted our shared appreciation for BBQ and fused the storied traditions of pit smoking and stout brewing.

Featuring barley smoked on our Primitive Pit smoker over New England maple and oak, Feed Your Soul.

node.text:
Tomorrow marks the return of an all-time favorite collaboration with our long-time friends at @row34!

As members of @northeastgrains and mutual fans of classic Belgian and French Saison, it was important to both parties that we honor tradition while utilizing local ingredients.

Brewed with 100% @valleymalt and hopped with gorgeous Czech Saaz, we made some thoughtful process tweaks that have brought batch two to new heights.

Nuanced, with layers of complexity, we're picking up notes of cracked white peppercorn, fresh-squeezed lemonade, toasted clove, black tea, and dried hay atop a lively effervescence and dry, crackling finish.

Bottles will be available to order online for Pickup and UPS Direct tomorrow at 9 AM. 7.0% ABV. $8.05/500ml bottle, no limits. Row34 will also have bottles available at their Fort Point and Burlington locations.

Pro-tip: Order a bottle with a dozen Island Creek Oysters and thank us later!
